wiki.text:
In modern molecular biology and genetics, the 'genome' is the entirety of an
organism's hereditary information. It is encoded either in DNA or, for many
types of viruses, in RNA.<ref>See also Gene</ref> The genome includes both the
genes and the non-coding sequences of the DNA/RNA.<ref>Ridley, M. (2006).
Genome. New York, NY: Harper Perennial. ISBN 0-06-019497-9</ref>
